WEBVTT

00:00.000 --> 00:03.720
(theme music playing)

01:06.680 --> 01:09.200
(crowd applauding on TV)

01:09.280 --> 01:12.160
(man on TV)<i> I do not believe that</i>
<i>any of us...</i>

01:12.880 --> 01:15.560
<i>would exchange places</i>
<i>with any other people</i>

01:15.640 --> 01:17.360
<i>or any other generation.</i>

01:18.400 --> 01:20.960
<i>The energy, the faith,</i>
<i>the devotion...</i>

01:21.040 --> 01:24.240
(Angela) <i>Grownups like to tell you where</i>
<i>they were when president Kennedy was shot,</i>

01:24.320 --> 01:26.320
<i>which they all know to the exact</i>
<i>second...</i>

01:27.200 --> 01:29.360
<i>which makes me almost jealous...</i>

01:30.520 --> 01:32.760
<i>like I should have</i>
<i>something important enough to know</i>

01:32.840 --> 01:36.720
<i>where I was when it happened...</i>
<i>but I don't yet.</i>

01:36.800 --> 01:39.400
(man on TV)<i> Ask what you can do</i>
<i>for your country.</i>

01:39.480 --> 01:41.640
(crowd applauding on TV)

01:45.800 --> 01:47.960
(Angela)<i> And the fact</i>
<i>that it was a better time then</i>

01:48.040 --> 01:51.560
<i>and people knew what they were supposed</i>
<i>to do and how to make the world better.</i>

01:52.200 --> 01:54.320
<i>Now nobody knows anything.</i>

01:55.440 --> 01:58.160
(thunder rumbling)

01:58.240 --> 02:01.400
<i>We know who's popular</i>
<i>or that social studies is boring...</i>

02:02.000 --> 02:04.280
<i>or that Brian always</i>
<i>has stomach trouble...</i>

02:08.200 --> 02:10.760
<i>but nobody knows</i>
<i>anything important.</i>

02:18.880 --> 02:22.440
Don't! Stop! I can't. Let go!
Please!

02:24.200 --> 02:26.960
(man on TV)<i> Strength and sacrifice,</i>
<i>which we ask of you.</i>

02:27.040 --> 02:28.720
(Angela)
<i>Instead of changing the world,</i>

02:28.800 --> 02:30.960
<i>people sit in class and write notes</i>
<i>about other people</i>

02:31.040 --> 02:33.000
(man on TV)
<i>Our only sure reward...</i>

02:34.880 --> 02:38.160
<i>with history the final</i>
<i>judge of our deeds...</i>

02:38.760 --> 02:41.640
(on TV)<i> Let us go forth</i>
<i>to lead the land we love...</i>

02:42.520 --> 02:45.560
<i>asking his blessing</i>
<i>and his help...</i>

02:46.480 --> 02:48.440
<i>but knowing that here on</i>
<i>earth...</i>

02:49.080 --> 02:51.960
<i>God's work must truly</i>
<i>be our own.</i>

02:52.040 --> 02:53.920
(gunshot)

03:00.760 --> 03:03.480
(intense music playing)

03:07.920 --> 03:10.880
(indistinct chatter)

03:16.760 --> 03:17.840
That's my soda!

03:19.840 --> 03:21.080
Gross!

03:21.640 --> 03:26.160
Get back! Get back! Get back!
Get back! Stay back! Be quiet!

03:27.160 --> 03:28.240
Did you see who it was?

03:30.920 --> 03:32.440
Did you?

03:32.520 --> 03:35.080
(tense music playing)

03:44.760 --> 03:46.160
I cannot believe it.

03:46.240 --> 03:49.160
That's the weirdest thing that
ever happened at this school ever.

03:49.240 --> 03:52.760
We were just sitting in our classrooms
just minding our own business.

03:52.840 --> 03:56.640
And look, I could have been right
at that spot.

03:56.720 --> 03:58.560
I was there, like, 10 minutes earlier.

03:58.640 --> 04:01.880
What's the big deal? It's not like
anybody even got a flesh wound.

04:01.960 --> 04:03.960
A bottle of soda
was shot tragically.

04:04.600 --> 04:06.440
I don't want our school
to have a reputation.

04:07.240 --> 04:08.680
Like yours, you mean?

04:10.280 --> 04:13.280
Everybody knows there's, like, 50 guns
in school at any given moment.

04:13.360 --> 04:17.640
The fact that they haven't gone off before
shows what a totally safe place this is.

04:18.920 --> 04:20.600
Give it a rest!

04:20.680 --> 04:22.480
Jeez! Excuse me.

04:23.280 --> 04:24.560
Excuse me.

04:27.400 --> 04:30.080
No one's going to get shot,
I promise.

04:30.160 --> 04:32.840
(indistinct conversations)

04:32.920 --> 04:34.280
Who'd write a note like that?

04:34.360 --> 04:37.400
Everybody writes notes like
that. We write notes like that.

04:37.480 --> 04:38.920
Yeah, We write notes
that are true.

04:39.800 --> 04:41.880
-This isn't true?
-Rayanne!

04:42.480 --> 04:45.000
-We barely made out.
-(Rayanne chuckles)

04:45.080 --> 04:46.360
You haven't been telling people.

04:46.440 --> 04:48.240
Oh, Angela, come on.
Hey, Rickie.

04:49.880 --> 04:52.080
I wouldn't blab about your
personal life, I promise you.

04:52.160 --> 04:53.240
What are you looking at?

04:55.920 --> 04:57.040
What happened to your shirt?

04:57.120 --> 04:59.200
It was nothing, it got caught on
the fence outside.

04:59.280 --> 05:01.480
-So can you believe all this?
-Did you see anything?

05:02.200 --> 05:03.840
No. I was in English.

05:03.920 --> 05:06.720
Maybe I should get a gun.
Bam! Bam!

05:06.800 --> 05:10.160
(indistinct conversations)

05:10.240 --> 05:12.800
When were you are in English?
You're scheduled for social studies.

05:12.880 --> 05:14.800
What's the difference?

05:14.880 --> 05:17.240
What's this I hear about you
and Jordan?

05:17.320 --> 05:20.480
-I can't believe this.
-You know they had sex.

05:20.560 --> 05:21.880
-Rayanne!
-That's what I heard.

05:21.960 --> 05:25.480
-(both chuckles)
-You, heard it too? God, just shoot me.

05:25.560 --> 05:28.600
-We could probably arrange that.
-You mean you didn't have sex?

05:28.680 --> 05:31.080
(Rayanne chuckles)
Angela, come on. Come.

05:33.280 --> 05:36.560
You've got to start thinking
of this as a positive thing.

05:36.640 --> 05:39.120
This could help you get
to the next level with Jordan.

05:39.840 --> 05:41.880
Okay, Did he at least think
you were a good kisser?

05:41.960 --> 05:44.360
-I don't know.
-Did you like the way he kissed?

05:45.200 --> 05:48.240
They weren't the kind of kisses
you could actually evaluate.

05:48.320 --> 05:52.400
They were...
introductory kisses.

05:52.480 --> 05:53.760
You should have had sex with him.

05:56.200 --> 05:57.600
(dog barks)

06:00.560 --> 06:01.600
(sighs)

06:03.640 --> 06:05.320
Where were you
when the gun went off?

06:05.400 --> 06:08.280
It wasn't anywhere near us.
We barely heard it.

06:09.240 --> 06:12.560
We have to worry about our kids
being shot in school.

06:12.640 --> 06:14.640
How did it come to this?

06:14.720 --> 06:15.560
This is horrible.

06:15.640 --> 06:18.560
-This is a disgrace to all of us.
-That's too much.

06:18.640 --> 06:22.720
I'm sorry, honey. I'm gonna say it
in this meeting, I'm, I mean it.

06:22.800 --> 06:24.160
We have to draw
the line somewhere.

06:24.240 --> 06:27.360
We can't just keep accepting
the total deterioration...

06:27.440 --> 06:29.400
The only thing shot
was a bottle of soda.

06:29.480 --> 06:32.360
I don't even know if you should
go there alone anymore.

06:32.440 --> 06:34.640
Maybe we should drop you
off every morning.

06:34.720 --> 06:36.400
-Dad.
-I know the gun was in the school.

06:36.480 --> 06:37.600
We can't be with her all day.

06:37.680 --> 06:40.200
We're not going to change
our entire lives over this.

06:40.280 --> 06:44.480
It was one stupid gunshot.
You're not dropping me at school.

06:44.560 --> 06:47.040
God! I'm not an 8-year-old.

06:47.640 --> 06:50.960
At my school, a kid slipped
on this wet spot, fell...

06:51.760 --> 06:52.840
like, on his face.

06:56.840 --> 06:58.840
Maybe we should take her
out of school...

06:59.760 --> 07:01.360
put her in private school.

07:01.440 --> 07:02.920
I wish we could afford that.

07:03.000 --> 07:06.480
Maybe that's not an excuse. Maybe
we should just sacrifice other things.

07:06.560 --> 07:08.280
Like the house in Palm Beach?

07:10.280 --> 07:12.480
This is our daughter
we're talking about.

07:13.680 --> 07:14.840
I know.

07:17.000 --> 07:18.640
I don't know
why the world's gone so crazy,

07:18.720 --> 07:20.520
and I don't know what to do about it.

07:22.040 --> 07:25.120
I wish we could... keep them
in some kind of bubble

07:25.200 --> 07:28.400
to protect them,
but, uh... I know we can't.

07:29.600 --> 07:31.720
I'm not asking for a bubble.

07:31.800 --> 07:36.120
How about just a place they can live
and walk to school and become grownups

07:36.200 --> 07:39.600
without having to worry about guns
and aids and serial murderers?

07:39.680 --> 07:42.960
That didn't used to be exotic.
That wasn't the province of the rich.

07:43.040 --> 07:47.200
We all had that...
why can't they have that?

07:48.720 --> 07:50.200
I don't know.

07:58.440 --> 07:59.680
(girl)
Stretch out.

07:59.760 --> 08:02.840
-(indistinct conversations)
-(whistle blows)

08:02.920 --> 08:05.400
Let's go, guys. Hustle. Come on,
hustle. Hustle. Hustle, concentrate.

08:05.480 --> 08:07.000
There. Did you see that?

08:08.160 --> 08:09.560
-See what?
-That guy.

08:10.080 --> 08:12.200
People are looking at me.

08:12.280 --> 08:14.640
-That's good.
-They're looking at me.

08:15.800 --> 08:17.960
Oh, they're looking at you.

08:18.040 --> 08:23.120
-(indistinct conversations)
-(team claps, cheers)

08:27.000 --> 08:28.640
-All right.
-Hi.

08:29.680 --> 08:31.400
Hi.

08:33.320 --> 08:36.840
See? What was that about?

08:36.920 --> 08:38.720
-He said hi.
-That was not hi.

08:39.360 --> 08:41.360
-That was a hi.
-That was a different hi.

08:42.080 --> 08:44.360
It was a...
he-wants-to-get-to-know-you hi.

08:44.440 --> 08:46.960
From someone who never talks
to me, has never talked to me,

08:47.040 --> 08:48.320
would never talk to me.

08:48.400 --> 08:50.960
Except now he thinks you
put out, so he talks to you.

08:51.560 --> 08:54.120
-I told you that note was good!
-Rayanne

08:55.080 --> 08:57.640
-(whistle blows)
-Let's slam!

08:59.440 --> 09:01.320
Maybe Jordan started the rumor.

09:01.880 --> 09:05.360
-Don't be ridiculous.
-That's it.

09:06.440 --> 09:08.360
It's a very guy thing to do.

09:10.520 --> 09:12.280
-Hey, Catalano.
-Hi.

09:12.920 --> 09:15.040
So what about this gun thing,
huh?

09:15.840 --> 09:18.560
I'd hate to be that soda bottle.
Splat!

09:18.640 --> 09:21.520
-(indistinct conversations)
-(intense music playing)

09:28.080 --> 09:29.200
Stop!

09:37.120 --> 09:38.680
Don't bug me, man!

09:38.760 --> 09:41.640
-(indistinct conversations)
-(intense music playing)

09:46.360 --> 09:47.880
So, do you know
what everyone's saying?

09:47.960 --> 09:51.240
-What?
-About you and Angela having sex.

09:51.840 --> 09:52.880
Who?

09:53.760 --> 09:56.200
-You and Angela.
-No. Who's saying that?

09:56.280 --> 10:00.120
People.
She told me the truth of course.

10:00.200 --> 10:01.680
What truth?

10:05.120 --> 10:06.600
How far you guys went.

10:07.600 --> 10:11.280
Well... yeah...
'cause nothing happened.

10:11.360 --> 10:13.560
All right,
so how come it's all over school?

10:14.640 --> 10:17.120
I mean, you're not talking it up
like some lowlife,

10:17.200 --> 10:20.680
derelict cretin telling everyone
you did her, are you?

10:20.760 --> 10:24.720
(indistinct conversations)

10:25.400 --> 10:26.800
Just checking.

10:29.160 --> 10:30.160
Hi, Brian.

10:30.960 --> 10:32.280
Hi.

10:33.400 --> 10:34.760
-This is Gina.
-Hey.

10:34.840 --> 10:37.720
-Right. Hi.
-Brian saw the entire thing.

10:37.800 --> 10:40.880
-I heard you chased the gunman.
-Chased the gunman?

10:40.960 --> 10:42.160
I would have just screamed.

10:42.240 --> 10:44.920
I have to leave the room
when my father uses the electric knife.

10:47.640 --> 10:50.080
Well, I think "Chase"
is a little bit strong,

10:50.160 --> 10:52.200
but, I was going to check out
the situation.

10:52.280 --> 10:54.080
Because If there's a gun...

10:55.320 --> 10:56.600
Mr. Foster.

10:56.680 --> 10:59.400
Mr. Krakow,
still getting those as?

10:59.480 --> 11:01.840
-Yes, sir.
-That's real good, Mr. Krakow.

11:01.920 --> 11:04.680
Come to my office for a few minutes.
I need to ask you few things.

11:04.760 --> 11:07.120
Well, actually, I have a class.

11:07.200 --> 11:09.800
You're excused from
your next class, Mr. Krakow.

11:09.880 --> 11:12.960
Oh, really? Great.
I mean, of course.

11:14.920 --> 11:16.200
(locker closes)

11:17.960 --> 11:20.840
(intense music playing)

11:25.200 --> 11:26.680
There she is.

11:26.760 --> 11:28.920
(bell ringing)

11:31.560 --> 11:33.640
(tense music playing)

11:58.360 --> 12:01.080
These are some grades. Have you
always gotten grades like this?

12:01.840 --> 12:03.120
Yes, sir.

12:03.200 --> 12:05.840
We need more kids
in our school like you, Brian.

12:05.920 --> 12:07.880
All the schools
need more kids like you.

12:08.800 --> 12:12.200
You're on a valedictorian path,
Mr. Krakow.

12:12.280 --> 12:15.520
All your teachers give you
an unqualified thumbs-up.

12:25.760 --> 12:27.840
So... what happened yesterday?

12:30.200 --> 12:31.640
Well, I already told
Mr. Higgins.

12:31.720 --> 12:33.640
But I'd like to hear it
from you.

12:34.240 --> 12:35.600
Right.

12:36.520 --> 12:38.440
I was leaving the bathroom,
and I heard a shot.

12:38.520 --> 12:40.320
You were in the bathroom
because...

12:41.600 --> 12:42.680
Because?

12:43.480 --> 12:46.120
-I... had to go to the bathroom.
-Which one?

12:46.840 --> 12:50.280
-The one by the...
-No, I meant what kind?

12:54.600 --> 12:56.520
How long were you
in the bathroom?

12:57.800 --> 13:00.000
Well, I didn't actually go.

13:00.800 --> 13:03.080
I had a stomach-ache,
but I didn't actually go.

13:03.160 --> 13:04.080
Because?

13:09.640 --> 13:11.280
because you heard something
in the hall.

13:13.240 --> 13:17.840
I heard a scuffle, but I didn't see anyone
when I came out. I just heard the shot.

13:18.960 --> 13:22.160
You heard a scuffle loud enough
to keep you from taking nature's call,

13:22.240 --> 13:24.600
but you didn't see anything.

13:26.600 --> 13:27.800
No, sir.

13:30.400 --> 13:32.920
Brian, I don't have to tell you
that this is a serious criminal act

13:33.000 --> 13:34.240
we're talking about here.

13:34.320 --> 13:35.360
Yes, sir.

13:35.440 --> 13:38.440
I'd hate to hear that you
were protecting someone...

13:39.200 --> 13:41.480
with your unblemished record
and all.

13:42.600 --> 13:44.400
I'm not protecting anyone.

13:53.760 --> 13:55.200
(door closes)

13:58.040 --> 14:01.120
(man) Ladies and gentlemen!
Ladies and gentlemen, please!

14:01.200 --> 14:02.800
for the safety of our children.

14:02.880 --> 14:06.960
Ladies and gentlemen, could I have
your undivided attention for one moment?

14:08.360 --> 14:12.480
Please can I have your attention?
Your undivided attention.

14:12.560 --> 14:13.640
(woman shushing)

14:16.080 --> 14:17.120
Thank you.

14:17.200 --> 14:19.160
I just wanted to let you know
some of the things

14:19.240 --> 14:22.760
we've been pursuing to ensure
a safe environment here at Liberty.

14:22.840 --> 14:24.840
We will not tolerate violence
in our schools.

14:24.920 --> 14:27.880
We will not accept it,
and we wouldn't mark to live with it.

14:27.960 --> 14:30.280
but all the safety measures in the world

14:30.360 --> 14:34.840
won't work unless I have
the cooperation of you, all of you.

14:34.920 --> 14:38.920
Yeah. People at these meetings are the
people who let their kids have guns.

14:39.000 --> 14:40.360
Are you getting the guns
out of school?

14:40.440 --> 14:42.600
That's the only question
that important to you.

14:43.520 --> 14:47.080
We're going to open this up for
your comments in just one moment. Please.

14:47.160 --> 14:49.800
My daughter has been in tears
for 36 hours.

14:49.880 --> 14:52.760
We're not going to live
with this terror in the school.

14:52.840 --> 14:54.240
One moment, please.

14:54.320 --> 14:58.120
We're getting nowhere fast
if each of us speaks out of turn.

14:58.200 --> 15:01.040
Now... as I was saying
to your point, Madame,

15:01.120 --> 15:03.920
Ms. Szowizki is going to provide
special counseling

15:04.000 --> 15:07.560
for any student who has
a problem coping with the incident.

15:07.640 --> 15:09.360
Ooh, that is good.

15:09.960 --> 15:13.160
Put the kids in therapy
so they can adjust to being shot.

15:13.240 --> 15:15.320
...what everybody has to say.

15:15.400 --> 15:17.360
If we could just say it
one at a time.

15:17.440 --> 15:18.800
Excuse me, Mr. Principal
could I just...

15:18.880 --> 15:23.040
What would help if everyone would say
your name and the name of your child's.

15:23.120 --> 15:26.200
My name's Amber Vallone.
I have a daughter, Rayanne Graff,

15:26.280 --> 15:29.040
who I leave in your capable
hands every day.

15:29.120 --> 15:34.040
I'd like to know, while you're bringing
in counsellors and being all upset,

15:34.120 --> 15:37.600
should I just send my daughter to school
in a bulletproof vest every day,

15:37.680 --> 15:42.720
or are you going to do something
about guns in school?

15:42.800 --> 15:46.960
It's not the lack of economic opportunity
or the poor home life

15:47.040 --> 15:51.200
or the lack of values, but the guns.
You know, the things that shoot.

15:51.280 --> 15:53.440
Are you going to get them
out of the school?

15:53.520 --> 15:57.960
(applauding)

15:58.880 --> 16:00.720
Yeah, I'd like to see it happen.

16:02.080 --> 16:04.800
Hey, you know, I really liked
what you had to say in there.

16:04.880 --> 16:06.400
(woman chuckles)

16:06.480 --> 16:10.560
-I wish that I could be that...
-What, loud? Obnoxious?

16:11.080 --> 16:12.200
Forceful.

16:13.000 --> 16:15.200
-I'm Patty Chase.
-Hi.

16:15.280 --> 16:19.280
-Angela's mom.
-Oh, wow! Angela!

16:19.360 --> 16:21.640
Rayanne talks about her
all the time.

16:21.720 --> 16:24.120
She's in love with her.
She wants to be Angela.

16:24.200 --> 16:27.760
Really? Gosh,
they seem so different.

16:27.840 --> 16:31.480
Kids find one person
and can't get enough of them.

16:31.560 --> 16:34.000
It's like being in love without
being allowed to have sex.

16:34.760 --> 16:36.520
-Right.
-(car engine starts)

16:36.600 --> 16:37.640
No, don't you remember?

16:37.720 --> 16:42.960
There'd be, like, this one person
who had, like, perfect hair

16:43.040 --> 16:46.680
or prefect breasts
or they were just so funny,

16:46.760 --> 16:48.440
and you just wanted
to eat them up,

16:48.520 --> 16:51.280
live in their bed,
and just be them.

16:51.360 --> 16:55.480
It's like everybody else was in black
and white and that person was in color.

16:56.280 --> 16:59.920
Rayanne thinks Angela
is in color, major color.

17:00.520 --> 17:01.680
Thanks.

17:02.640 --> 17:05.960
So, how is Rayanne handling
this whole incident?

17:07.360 --> 17:09.240
She's great.
I'm the basket case.

17:09.320 --> 17:10.920
Angela's just the same.

17:11.000 --> 17:14.080
"Who's going to shoot me
with this bod, ma," she says.

17:14.160 --> 17:17.360
They think they're immortal, and
they have other things on their mind.

17:18.120 --> 17:19.720
(woman yells)

17:19.800 --> 17:23.280
Speaking of which,
Jordan is unbelievable.

17:23.360 --> 17:25.720
Your daughter has complete
taste.

17:28.240 --> 17:29.440
Excuse me.

17:29.520 --> 17:31.720
Rayanne showed me
his yearbook picture.

17:31.800 --> 17:33.800
If I were Angela
running around with him,

17:33.880 --> 17:36.480
I wouldn't give a damn about
guns in this school either.

17:37.800 --> 17:44.040
So you think that... Jordan has...
gotten in the way for Angela?

17:44.120 --> 17:47.320
And she was so obsessed
with him all that time,

17:47.400 --> 17:49.880
and wham bam!
It's actually happening,

17:49.960 --> 17:51.280
but we know
what that's like, right?

17:51.360 --> 17:53.240
Young love or lust.

17:53.320 --> 17:55.160
-What's the difference?
-(Patty chuckles)

17:56.080 --> 17:58.040
-Wham bam!
-Yeah!

17:59.280 --> 18:01.200
-Jordan.
-Hmm.

18:01.280 --> 18:05.960
I could have died. I did die.
This woman knows, and I don't know.

18:06.040 --> 18:09.640
She not a woman. She's this
40-year-old girl. She's gorgeous.

18:09.720 --> 18:13.280
