The girl talked to her mother.
We don't know if it's true.

18:18.720 --> 18:20.840
These things are always true.
Of course, it's true.

18:20.920 --> 18:23.760
-Here, taste this.
-I couldn't taste anything.

18:23.840 --> 18:27.280
Guns are going off at school,
Angela's sleeping with someone.

18:27.360 --> 18:28.440
You don't know that.

18:28.880 --> 18:29.880
How is it?

18:29.960 --> 18:32.800
Even if she isn't,
which I pray is true...

18:33.480 --> 18:36.880
she obviously has some sort
of secret life completely apart from us.

18:36.960 --> 18:38.480
-This is wonderful.
-Cilantro.

18:41.440 --> 18:43.000
So, what do we do?

18:43.840 --> 18:45.720
-Do we confront her?
-Oh, God, no.

18:46.960 --> 18:49.040
I don't want to know
if it's true.

18:50.480 --> 18:52.800
What sort of attitude
are we supposed to have?

18:52.880 --> 18:54.280
Are we supposed to have
an attitude?

18:54.360 --> 18:57.400
I already have an attitude.
Maybe my mother's attitude.

18:58.240 --> 18:59.800
I don't want to get hysterical
about this.

18:59.880 --> 19:03.600
Why shouldn't I be hysterical?
She's 15. I should be hysterical.

19:03.680 --> 19:05.680
(Angela) Danielle, if you have
my sweatshirt, I'll kill you.

19:05.760 --> 19:07.000
You understand me?

19:09.320 --> 19:11.200
-Can I taste whatever it is?
-Sure.

19:15.560 --> 19:17.560
-Cilantro. I love that.
-Very good.

19:17.640 --> 19:19.400
I thought with the tomato
it would sharpen it a bit.

19:19.480 --> 19:20.880
I think it's great.

19:20.960 --> 19:22.360
Is that the phyllo stuff?

19:22.920 --> 19:24.960
Honey... who's Jordan?

19:26.640 --> 19:27.640
No one.

19:30.160 --> 19:33.320
-You mean Jordan Catalano?
-Is that his last name?

19:33.400 --> 19:34.880
I don't know. You brought it up.

19:36.160 --> 19:37.880
I met Rayanne's mom tonight.

19:37.960 --> 19:40.760
She was excited about your new
boyfriend, Jordan.

19:40.840 --> 19:43.120
Boyfriend? That's a laugh.

19:43.200 --> 19:46.520
-He's not your boyfriend?
-I barely know this person.

19:47.480 --> 19:49.480
I don't know
if I want to know this person.

19:50.240 --> 19:53.520
-Well, then, you haven't...
-What did you hear?

19:55.160 --> 19:56.560
What did she tell you?

19:57.680 --> 19:59.000
Nothing.
She didn't tell me anything.

19:59.080 --> 20:01.040
Did she say I was sleeping
with Jordan Catalano?

20:01.120 --> 20:03.040
No! I mean, no, of course not.

20:03.120 --> 20:06.520
No one said that.
That's just... well, I just wondered.

20:06.600 --> 20:07.600
She did.

20:08.920 --> 20:10.400
I can't believe this.

20:11.000 --> 20:12.440
I can't believe this.

20:13.320 --> 20:14.760
I hate everyone.

20:18.840 --> 20:20.400
Obviously, I told my mother.

20:20.480 --> 20:22.440
But all I said was that,
you were hot for him.

20:22.520 --> 20:25.520
-Why even tell her that?
-My mother thinks we slept together.

20:26.880 --> 20:28.880
Okay. Do you want my mother
to call your mother

20:28.960 --> 20:30.520
and tell her you didn't sleep together?

20:32.560 --> 20:34.080
Well, I can do that.

20:38.360 --> 20:39.880
-Hi, honey.
-Hey, fag.

20:39.960 --> 20:41.160
Go to hell.

20:41.720 --> 20:43.400
Meet me later.
I'll have something for you.

20:43.480 --> 20:45.080
Is that perfume I smell?

20:45.160 --> 20:47.000
You know you're boring,
don't you?

20:48.720 --> 20:49.920
Turd head, you need some.

20:50.600 --> 20:53.360
Yo, Graff, why don't you come
driving with us tonight?

20:53.440 --> 20:55.640
That would be exciting...
if I were in a coma.

20:56.360 --> 20:58.520
It'll be exciting. Later.

20:58.600 --> 21:02.440
-(indistinct conversations)
-(lockers clicking)

21:02.520 --> 21:03.800
I could have handled that.

21:05.440 --> 21:06.680
Yeah, you were doing great.

21:07.560 --> 21:11.840
I'm asking a particular
question, is it fair?

21:12.760 --> 21:14.280
What does "fair"
have to do with it?

21:14.360 --> 21:16.080
"Fair" has to do with... what?

21:16.840 --> 21:17.840
Anybody.

21:18.520 --> 21:21.280
"Fair" has to do with the right to come
to school and be able to work

21:21.360 --> 21:23.320
and not be terrified,

21:23.400 --> 21:26.520
not have your heart beating fast,
not jump at every loud noise.

21:28.200 --> 21:31.280
The right to come in
and be left alone.

21:31.360 --> 21:34.360
-No?
-Maybe not everybody's left alone anyway.

21:34.440 --> 21:35.640
Meaning what?

21:35.720 --> 21:37.320
You don't know
what goes on around here. Okay.

21:37.400 --> 21:41.040
Maybe some people have guns
for, like, to protect yourself.

21:42.160 --> 21:44.960
Maybe some people who have
guns are, like, victims, too...

21:45.440 --> 21:47.600
and they're, like,
forced to carry.

21:47.680 --> 21:50.960
You think kids with guns
are like gangsters or dealers.

21:51.040 --> 21:53.360
But you are saying that,
If somebody's threatened,

21:53.440 --> 21:55.280
it's okay to carry a gun
in school?

21:55.360 --> 21:57.120
You don't think school
authorities can protect them?

21:57.200 --> 22:00.440
Man, you don't know
what goes on around here. Yes!

22:00.520 --> 22:04.480
If I was... say I was threatened,
and I'm not saying that I am...

22:05.400 --> 22:09.040
I'd be packing in no time,
no time at all.

22:09.120 --> 22:12.760
(mellow music playing)

22:12.840 --> 22:15.240
(teacher) Very clearly stated.

22:17.160 --> 22:19.160
So what do the rest of you think
of what he just said?

22:20.160 --> 22:22.760
Should people take the law
into their own hands like that?

22:24.000 --> 22:25.200
I mean, is that the answer?

22:26.080 --> 22:27.280
Does that solve anything?

22:27.960 --> 22:31.400
Anyone. Ang-Angela... Angela?

22:33.280 --> 22:37.360
(intense music playing)

22:43.160 --> 22:45.800
My So Called Life
<i>will continue here on ABC.</i>

23:00.840 --> 23:02.440
Right before the gun went off,

23:02.520 --> 23:04.680
I was thinking about how
much I wanted that soda.

23:04.760 --> 23:07.320
Is that weird, why did I leave
with you in the first place.

23:07.400 --> 23:10.600
And what if I'd gone to get it
right at that moment?

23:10.680 --> 23:14.160
Oh, my God.
I better change my locker.

23:14.960 --> 23:17.000
What happens
when you don't sleep?

23:17.080 --> 23:20.080
I haven't slept since it happened.
It keeps coming back to me.

23:20.160 --> 23:22.400
It keeps coming back...
what was that?

23:24.320 --> 23:26.680
I just keep going over
in my mind.

23:27.480 --> 23:30.960
All my friends go by that locker
all the time. It's just...

23:31.040 --> 23:34.160
It's not even me. If somebody
had been going by there and...

23:35.200 --> 23:36.240
gotten shot.

23:36.880 --> 23:38.360
It's hard, isn't it?

23:39.240 --> 23:42.160
You don't think I could get
a... few days off, do you?

23:44.800 --> 23:46.040
Yeah. Catch you later, dude.

23:46.120 --> 23:50.400
(indistinct conversations)

23:53.960 --> 23:56.280
You're here again because
I wanted to hear your story,

23:56.360 --> 23:58.320
and detective Martinson wanted
to hear it too.

23:58.400 --> 24:00.160
I don't have anything
else to tell.

24:00.640 --> 24:02.200
Mr. Krakow,
can I tell you something?

24:03.520 --> 24:05.200
This is a good school.

24:05.280 --> 24:08.080
We want to keep it a good
school... You know what I mean?

24:08.160 --> 24:10.640
-Yes, sir.
-No, you don't, son.

24:11.520 --> 24:14.520
I've got these officers here
and the school board,

24:14.600 --> 24:18.360
the newspapers and the
television and a lot of nasty,

24:18.440 --> 24:21.360
angry parents who want to know
something about what happened.

24:21.440 --> 24:23.880
You are the person
who knows that something.

24:23.960 --> 24:28.040
Now you are standing between me
and my ability to keep this a good school.

24:28.120 --> 24:32.600
And I don't like it when people
do things to my school.

24:32.680 --> 24:33.680
You get my meaning?

24:34.760 --> 24:38.960
So tell us, what was the noise that caused
you to come out of the bathroom?

24:40.960 --> 24:43.240
(indistinct conversations)

24:43.320 --> 24:46.680
-Hey, Brian, how you doing?
-You actually know my name.

24:46.760 --> 24:48.400
Of course, I know your name.

24:48.920 --> 24:50.160
How they treating you Brian?

24:50.240 --> 24:53.560
Baseball bats, electrodes attached
to various parts of your anatomy?

24:53.640 --> 24:55.560
Excuse me. I have a class.

24:55.640 --> 24:57.400
Just remember
what happens to snitches.

25:00.760 --> 25:02.920
Hey, Brian, are you okay?

25:03.000 --> 25:04.000
Yeah. Sure.

25:04.080 --> 25:06.200
I'm sorry you're the person
that has to deal with this.

25:06.280 --> 25:08.760
-No problem.
-Because if you saw something,

25:08.840 --> 25:10.960
somebody really had a gun,
you should tell them.

25:11.040 --> 25:14.600
Otherwise you would be like part
of it. People are really scared, Brian.

25:14.680 --> 25:15.480
You should tell them,

25:15.560 --> 25:20.520
and you shouldn't feel bad about
that because people will thank you.

25:22.360 --> 25:24.280
-Hi, Brian.
-What?

25:24.360 --> 25:26.440
I was thinking, this all thing
about this gun and all.

25:26.520 --> 25:28.720
It really make an important
outcome for the paper.

25:28.800 --> 25:31.760
So, I was thinking that. You and
I should do an interview sometime.

25:31.840 --> 25:34.200
To let people know
what really happened.

25:34.280 --> 25:36.560
Maybe sometime after school.
What do you think?

25:36.640 --> 25:38.000
What?

25:39.040 --> 25:40.120
See you later.

25:43.480 --> 25:46.040
Has the threat of violence changed
the quality of my life at school?

25:46.720 --> 25:48.440
No, not really.
What do you mean?

25:49.360 --> 25:51.360
I don't see the point
of talking about it.

25:52.280 --> 25:54.720
Sometimes talking about
it makes people feel better.

25:55.200 --> 25:57.320
And sometimes talking
gets people into trouble.

25:57.400 --> 25:59.240
(telephone rings indistinctly)

26:00.760 --> 26:04.160
You know, people say things about people.
It doesn't mean it's true.

26:04.240 --> 26:07.480
-About who might be carrying a gun?
-About anything.

26:08.320 --> 26:09.320
Any weapon?

26:09.400 --> 26:12.200
No! Just about anything
anybody says about people.

26:13.520 --> 26:14.800
It's not always true.

26:15.840 --> 26:18.160
I think people want to believe
things about people,

26:18.240 --> 26:20.520
so they decide certain
things are true.

26:20.600 --> 26:23.720
And they don't even ask.
And it's not fair!

26:25.320 --> 26:27.000
'Cause you have to live with it
anyway.

26:27.560 --> 26:30.200
But if it's not true, the person
could always say that, couldn't they?

26:30.880 --> 26:35.160
I think if something is false, people
aren't going to keep on believing it.

26:35.240 --> 26:38.880
Usually people latch onto things
when there's a kernel of truth.

26:38.960 --> 26:40.560
That's when they get
into trouble.

26:43.240 --> 26:46.640
<i>-♪ Though my dreams ♪</i>
-(knock on door)

26:46.720 --> 26:49.240
<i>♪ It's never quite as it seems ♪</i>

26:49.320 --> 26:50.320
Knock-knock.

26:50.400 --> 26:52.440
<i>♪ Never quite as it seems ♪</i>

26:52.520 --> 26:53.760
Hi.

26:56.520 --> 26:58.240
<i>♪ I know I've felt like this</i>
<i>Before... ♪</i>

26:58.320 --> 26:59.720
Mind if I, um...

27:00.560 --> 27:03.240
-Might as well turn it off.
-No...

27:04.480 --> 27:05.520
I like it.

27:05.600 --> 27:11.360
(music playing)

27:21.960 --> 27:23.040
This is hard.

27:24.880 --> 27:26.000
We need to talk.

27:26.080 --> 27:29.560
(Angela)<i> When I was 12,</i>
<i>my mother gave me my sex talk.</i>

27:29.640 --> 27:32.040
<i>I doubt either of us</i>
<i>has fully recovered.</i>

27:32.120 --> 27:34.800
Now that you and Jordan are,
um...

27:34.880 --> 27:38.000
-Oh, my God. Mom, please.
-Angela,

27:38.080 --> 27:41.160
-I can accept that you have a boyfriend.
-I don't have a boyfriend.

27:41.240 --> 27:44.640
Fine... A pal. A male pal.

27:45.120 --> 27:47.480
Whatever word you want
to choose. The point is...

27:48.880 --> 27:50.760
I'm your mother,
and I don't think you're ready.

27:50.840 --> 27:52.720
-Mom, please!
-I don't think you're ready.

27:52.800 --> 27:56.240
But... I have to know
if this is what's happening

27:56.320 --> 27:59.240
because... I don't think
I can keep you...

27:59.320 --> 28:03.320
-Mom, I beg you to stop.
-I need to know you're using...

28:03.400 --> 28:06.360
I mean, I remember
how this feels. I do.

28:06.440 --> 28:09.640
But... it's the times
that we live in.

28:09.720 --> 28:11.960
-Mom, please.
-Honey,

28:12.040 --> 28:13.760
I know you don't want to think
about these things.

28:13.840 --> 28:16.360
-I know, you think you're invulnerable...
-I don't think that.

28:16.440 --> 28:21.200
You have to use some kind of protection
if you're going to be...

28:21.280 --> 28:24.240
Mom, I'm not having sex,
all right?

28:24.320 --> 28:28.240
Really... I'm not even close
to an embarrassing degree.

28:29.960 --> 28:33.040
(Patty sighs)

28:33.560 --> 28:34.640
Okay.

28:36.600 --> 28:38.320
I'm sorry, honey. I just...

28:41.080 --> 28:44.680
I just... I want you to be
prepared when the time comes.

28:44.760 --> 28:46.320
Whenever the time comes.

28:46.400 --> 28:49.120
It'll never come.
Not with Jordan.

28:51.160 --> 28:53.840
-Is that what's bothering you?
-No! Nothing's bothering me.

28:53.920 --> 28:55.280
Something's bothering you.

28:55.360 --> 28:59.080
Mom, you couldn't possibly
understand or help, so please.

28:59.160 --> 29:01.680
I don't mean to hurt
your feelings, but just please.

29:06.560 --> 29:10.000
(music playing in background)

29:10.080 --> 29:11.560
I'm here if you need me.

29:12.520 --> 29:13.840
You know that.

29:13.920 --> 29:20.600
-(music continues in background)
-(thunder rumbling)

29:46.320 --> 29:48.560
-That's good to know about.
-Yeah.

29:49.760 --> 29:52.200
My uncle choked
on a chicken bone.

29:52.280 --> 29:54.000
(Angela)
<i>That's when the change happened.</i>

29:54.760 --> 29:55.840
<i>Just like that.</i>

29:57.080 --> 30:00.720
<i>Somewhere in those few seconds,</i>
<i>I knew my life would never be the same.</i>

30:00.800 --> 30:01.840
Did he survive?

30:02.760 --> 30:04.040
Yeah.

30:04.120 --> 30:06.280
(Angela) <i>I knew then</i>
<i>that the rumor was right.</i>

30:07.240 --> 30:10.680
<i>Not in actuality, but in my</i>
<i>heart because at that moment,</i>

30:10.760 --> 30:13.840
I would've done anything,
I wanted him so much.

30:13.920 --> 30:16.240
I didn't say anything about...

30:17.320 --> 30:18.680
-you know.
-I know.

30:18.760 --> 30:22.120
-I just wanted you to know that.
-Thank you.

30:22.840 --> 30:24.200
Because I'm not like that.

30:25.240 --> 30:26.880
-I don't do that.
-No.

30:28.000 --> 30:31.680
-It's so weird, huh?
-Yeah. Yeah.

30:31.760 --> 30:33.440
I mean, the way people talk.

30:34.000 --> 30:36.200
I mean...
people think we did it.

30:36.280 --> 30:37.280
I know.

30:38.920 --> 30:41.720
It's like we might as well have
done it anyway at this point.

30:44.000 --> 30:45.360
I mean at least...

30:46.240 --> 30:48.760
I mean, if everybody's
talking about it already...

30:49.440 --> 30:50.720
maybe we, uh...

30:52.640 --> 30:55.000
I mean, not to make a big deal
out of it or anything.

30:56.200 --> 30:57.680
-Out of what?
-Out of...

30:58.840 --> 31:00.240
Out of anything.

31:01.120 --> 31:02.480
I mean, if everybody's...

31:03.880 --> 31:05.320
already assuming it anyway...

31:06.720 --> 31:09.200
maybe... we should...

31:10.320 --> 31:11.320
just...

31:11.800 --> 31:14.160
(Angela) <i>It's amazing the things</i>
<i>you notice.</i>

31:14.920 --> 31:17.920
<i>Like the corner of his collar</i>
<i>that was coming undone.</i>

31:18.000 --> 31:21.400
<i>Like he was from a poor family</i>
<i>and couldn't afford new shirts.</i>

31:22.240 --> 31:23.760
<i>That's all I could see.</i>

31:23.840 --> 31:27.080
<i>The whole world was that</i>
<i>unraveled piece of fabric.</i>

31:27.160 --> 31:28.240
I think...

31:30.520 --> 31:31.760
I have to go.

31:32.880 --> 31:35.040
-Look, I'm sorry if I...
-No, it's okay.

31:35.120 --> 31:37.040
-No pressure or anything.
-I have to go.

31:37.120 --> 31:38.400
You could just think about it.

31:39.120 --> 31:41.600
(Angela) <i>It's such a lie that you should</i>
<i>do what's in your heart.</i>

31:42.360 --> 31:46.000
<i>If we all did what was in our hearts,</i>
<i>the world would grind to a halt.</i>

31:46.080 --> 31:48.240
(water running, stops)

31:59.680 --> 32:03.320
And they know that he knows.
I can't believe he didn't tell them.

32:03.400 --> 32:04.920
He got a perfect
score on his PSATs.

32:05.000 --> 32:07.280
You believe that.
Now it will be ruined.

32:07.360 --> 32:08.920
What does this have
to do with Angela?

32:09.000 --> 32:10.480
They would have sex.

32:10.560 --> 32:12.560
Her and Jordan
had sex at Brian's house.

32:12.640 --> 32:14.200
Oh, my God. Can you believe it.

32:14.280 --> 32:15.320
Right, In the front yard.

32:15.400 --> 32:17.840
Brian watched the entire thing
through his kitchen window.

32:17.920 --> 32:20.280
Aren't you and Angela tight?

32:21.360 --> 32:22.920
She was, like, my best friend.

32:23.760 --> 32:25.640
This whole thing has been
hard for me to accept.

32:26.400 --> 32:31.800
But Brian wouldn't lie,
so... it's like... it's like she's this...

32:32.760 --> 32:35.120
it's like she's this completely
different person.

32:35.600 --> 32:39.880
-Like a slut?
-No. No. No, she's not.

32:40.400 --> 32:44.320
I think she's just, like,
confused or something.

32:44.400 --> 32:47.760
(bell ringing)

32:50.720 --> 32:52.360
(door closes)

33:03.320 --> 33:05.480
-So, you want me to kill her?
-No. It doesn't matter.

33:05.560 --> 33:07.360
It's Brian who should be killed.

33:07.440 --> 33:08.920
He should definitely die.

33:09.000 --> 33:10.440
He's going to rat on Rickie.

33:10.520 --> 33:12.880
What is there actually
to rat on Rickie? Do you know?

33:13.800 --> 33:16.000
Whatever he did
he did 'cause he had to.

33:16.520 --> 33:19.640
You haven't cleaned him up after some
Neanderthal beats the hell out of him.

33:26.920 --> 33:28.240
Come here for a minute, son.

33:32.240 --> 33:35.840
-Rickie Vasquez, familiar with the name?
-Excuse me?

33:36.360 --> 33:38.720
What can you tell me, son,
about Rickie Vasquez?

33:40.640 --> 33:41.720
He goes here?

33:43.040 --> 33:45.520
I don't... I mean...

33:46.920 --> 33:50.480
did you hear something...
Did he see something about the gun?

33:52.360 --> 33:55.760
Mr. Krakow, I'm going to tell
you about a legal term.

33:55.840 --> 33:57.880
It's called accessory
after the fact.

33:57.960 --> 33:59.600
I don't like accessories
after the fact.

33:59.680 --> 34:01.280
I don't want them in my school.

34:01.360 --> 34:03.800
You'll come to my office at three o'clock

34:03.880 --> 34:07.200
and tell me everything you know about
Rickie Vasquez

34:07.280 --> 34:10.040
and anyone else who might
be involved in this incident.

34:10.120 --> 34:13.240
If you don't,
regardless of your grade scores,

34:13.320 --> 34:15.800
you may not be going
to this school much longer.

34:16.600 --> 34:17.960
You get my clear intent?

34:19.040 --> 34:20.080
Yes, sir.

34:20.800 --> 34:21.800
Good.

