34:39.800 --> 34:42.480
-What?
-I don't even want to talk to you.

34:42.560 --> 34:43.880
Then don't.

34:44.680 --> 34:47.560
-Did Rickie have the gun?
-Give me a break. God, Angela.

34:47.640 --> 34:49.640
You don't know
the whole situation.

34:49.960 --> 34:52.080
-I don't want him hurt.
-Him hurt?

34:56.080 --> 34:57.080
What about me?

34:58.760 --> 35:00.160
This is the police now.

35:00.240 --> 35:02.720
Should I get expelled protecting
someone I don't even know?

35:02.800 --> 35:04.080
Don't ask me.

35:04.680 --> 35:06.000
Nobody's interested
in the truth.

35:06.680 --> 35:09.600
Nobody is interested in truth. All they
care about is what they want to believe.

35:09.680 --> 35:12.360
If you're concerned with the
truth, Why did you lie about me?

35:12.440 --> 35:15.440
-You name don't even come up.
-Not the gun thing, to Sharon.

35:16.280 --> 35:18.360
What you said to her about
me and Jordan Catalano.

35:18.440 --> 35:20.600
-What are you talking about?
-I heard her, Brian.

35:21.520 --> 35:25.960
You told her terrible things.
False things. You lied to her.

35:33.080 --> 35:34.600
I didn't lie to her. I just...

35:38.800 --> 35:41.320
What difference does it make?
I can imagine what she did with it.

35:45.720 --> 35:47.560
But it's just...
that you lied, too,

35:48.520 --> 35:51.240
when you said you didn't know anything
about Jordan coming over that night.

35:51.680 --> 35:53.920
Because I've thought about
it for like 50 hours.

35:55.080 --> 35:57.600
You knew it, didn't you?
You used me.

35:57.680 --> 35:59.000
It's not the same.

35:59.080 --> 36:01.240
Maybe it is,
because you did what you wanted.

36:01.320 --> 36:03.760
You didn't care about what
damaged it did to anybody else.

36:03.840 --> 36:06.120
What damage did it do to you?

36:09.280 --> 36:13.160
(thunder continues rumbling)

36:16.120 --> 36:17.480
Angela?

36:19.840 --> 36:20.840
Angela.

36:21.520 --> 36:22.800
Can I talk to you for a second?

36:23.920 --> 36:27.120
-How you doing?
-You know. Life goes on.

36:27.200 --> 36:30.000
I was thinking about
what I said to you yesterday.

36:30.080 --> 36:33.800
-You know, the thing.
-Right. The thing.

36:33.880 --> 36:35.320
Look, I'm sorry about that.

36:35.400 --> 36:39.120
Afterwards I thought it through,
and I could see how you got upset...

36:39.200 --> 36:41.400
-No, I wasn't upset.
-Some girls wouldn't be,

36:41.480 --> 36:43.440
but... you're not like that,

36:43.520 --> 36:47.440
so... I just wanted to say...
I'm sorry.

36:48.160 --> 36:51.160
No. It's really okay.
I mean, it wasn't a problem.

36:51.240 --> 36:53.440
Really, I didn't think about it.

36:56.600 --> 36:59.000
I mean, I did think about it,
and I thought...

36:59.880 --> 37:02.320
maybe what you were
saying wasn't so wrong.

37:02.400 --> 37:04.400
-No. It was really wrong.
-Why?

37:04.480 --> 37:06.920
And I just want to let you know,
that if it'll make you feel better,

37:07.640 --> 37:12.040
I'll make it clear that I don't have
any real interest in you or anything...

37:13.200 --> 37:15.960
so they'll stop saying that.

37:16.600 --> 37:19.200
(bell ringing)

37:19.280 --> 37:22.200
You know, that I barely even know you,
which is, of course, true,

37:22.280 --> 37:26.360
and that basically, you and I
mean nothing to each other.

37:29.160 --> 37:32.880
-So that should solve the problem.
-Thanks.

37:35.720 --> 37:37.440
It's the least I can do,
you know.

37:38.760 --> 37:39.760
Right.

37:45.520 --> 37:50.360
-(serene music playing)
-(siren blaring at distance)

38:07.080 --> 38:09.160
-Hey.
-Hey.

38:10.080 --> 38:11.280
Whatcha doing out here?

38:12.360 --> 38:13.520
It's what I always do.

38:13.600 --> 38:15.320
I can't make it through
a whole day in there.

38:15.400 --> 38:16.760
I know what you mean.

38:17.320 --> 38:19.120
Yeah. What do you need
to hide from?

38:19.840 --> 38:23.120
-Your life is perfect. I'm serious.
-(scoffs)

38:23.880 --> 38:25.600
I would give anything
to have your life.

38:27.080 --> 38:30.840
-My life is so pathetic.
-You have this great house...

38:31.560 --> 38:33.200
parents that are, like, there...

38:34.120 --> 38:35.760
and no one bothers you
at school.

38:36.120 --> 38:38.600
Rickie, I need to talk to you
about the gun.

38:39.000 --> 38:40.040
Don't.

38:40.600 --> 38:43.240
-You can't carry a gun, Rickie.
-I don't.

38:43.320 --> 38:44.680
'Cause it'd be really bad.

38:45.520 --> 38:48.880
-Tragically bad.
-Angela, I don't carry a gun.

38:48.960 --> 38:50.600
I wouldn't even know
how to shoot one.

38:52.040 --> 38:53.280
But didn't Brian see you?

38:54.200 --> 38:55.680
Isn't that what
he's going to tell them?

38:58.000 --> 39:01.120
This is really serious. People will think
you're a dangerous person.

39:01.200 --> 39:02.200
I know.

39:03.080 --> 39:04.240
That's what I want.

39:06.800 --> 39:07.880
So what did happen?

39:11.280 --> 39:13.600
My cousin brought it
in to sell it...

39:14.520 --> 39:17.280
and I got real mad at him
for bringing a gun into school.

39:18.560 --> 39:20.640
So we got into this
big argument.

39:21.680 --> 39:24.760
The next thing I knew, the thing
fell out of the box and went off.

39:26.360 --> 39:28.280
And he peed in his pants
and ran away.

39:29.760 --> 39:33.040
-He did not.
-He did. Big stain.

39:33.120 --> 39:34.680
(Rickie, Angela chuckles)

39:34.760 --> 39:36.680
And that's what happened
with the gun?

39:37.600 --> 39:39.400
That's the whole story
of the gun.

39:45.240 --> 39:47.120
And now Brian's going
to say you did it.

39:48.560 --> 39:50.280
I'm telling you, I hope he does.

39:51.120 --> 39:53.200
No. Don't be stupid.

39:56.600 --> 39:57.640
You know, it's weird.

39:59.840 --> 40:03.040
(mellow music playing)

40:03.120 --> 40:07.480
I always think of you
as... Rayanne's friend.

40:09.520 --> 40:12.880
I mean, like...
you just think of me as...

40:16.360 --> 40:20.200
as someone who's just...
you know, around.

40:22.640 --> 40:25.360
(Angela) <i>It's weird how something</i>
<i>has to happen sometimes...</i>

40:26.760 --> 40:29.320
<i>to see how you actually</i>
<i>feel about someone.</i>

40:29.400 --> 40:35.200
-(serene music playing)
-(bell ringing)

40:50.360 --> 40:53.560
Sit down, Mr. Krakow. We're just waiting
for our friends from law enforcement.

41:00.000 --> 41:02.480
Could you imagine Rickie
in a high-security prison?

41:02.560 --> 41:03.720
Who'd supply his makeup?

41:03.800 --> 41:06.120
Could it might be possibly not
make everything into a joke?

41:06.200 --> 41:08.920
Angela, there is nothing
to worry about.

41:09.880 --> 41:11.440
Harlan, this guy Tino knows...

41:11.520 --> 41:14.000
he's been arrested
with a gun twice,

41:14.080 --> 41:15.320
and nothing ever happened.

41:16.160 --> 41:17.200
It's no big deal.

41:18.720 --> 41:20.080
Know what I would really like?

41:21.240 --> 41:25.760
-To be put out of my misery.
-Are you kidding? This is fun!

41:25.840 --> 41:26.960
Fun?

41:27.040 --> 41:30.320
Everyone running around
all upset, rumor's flying.

41:30.400 --> 41:33.080
Can't you feel it
in your fingers and your toes?

41:33.160 --> 41:35.280
It's like... being alive.

41:36.360 --> 41:39.000
-Man, it's such a rush.
-You're out of your mind.

41:39.960 --> 41:40.760
Last year,

41:40.840 --> 41:43.800
that rumor about me and Mark Hammer in
the orchestra pit during the talent show?

41:44.520 --> 41:48.840
In that case, it was true. But...
man, all that conversation.

41:49.320 --> 41:53.120
People writing notes, and they...
look at you different,

41:53.200 --> 41:55.760
trying to figure out
who you really are.

41:55.840 --> 41:57.360
Like you're famous.

41:58.600 --> 41:59.720
Admit it.

42:00.560 --> 42:01.560
It's really great.

42:02.320 --> 42:04.080
I don't know
what you're talking about.

42:06.520 --> 42:12.040
(indistinct conversations)

42:18.080 --> 42:19.560
Come in, gentlemen.

42:26.600 --> 42:28.000
So, Mr. Krakow.

42:33.480 --> 42:34.920
I've thought a lot about
what you said,

42:35.000 --> 42:37.400
and I've decided the main thing
is to protect the school.

42:38.680 --> 42:39.920
That's good, Brian.

42:41.240 --> 42:42.520
I went to the bathroom...

42:43.640 --> 42:46.400
I heard a scuffle, then a shot.
I came out.

42:47.000 --> 42:49.600
I saw two pairs of legs
running in opposite directions.

42:50.440 --> 42:52.280
Who those people
were I can't say.

42:53.960 --> 42:59.520
And if you... or these men...
or anybody else threatens me anymore

42:59.600 --> 43:00.960
-or pressures me anymore...
-Brian...

43:01.040 --> 43:02.960
I will insist on having
a lawyer,

43:03.040 --> 43:06.480
and I will sue you for harassment
and anything else I can.

43:06.560 --> 43:10.520
If you try to expel me to solve
your public relations problems,

43:10.600 --> 43:12.680
I will reveal to anyone who will listen,

43:12.760 --> 43:14.840
just who is destroying
the spirit of this school.

43:23.160 --> 43:24.200
Hey.

43:31.200 --> 43:33.960
So they still haven't found
out who had the gun.

43:34.040 --> 43:36.240
Mom, it's okay. Let it go.

43:36.320 --> 43:38.280
The school hasn't
self-destructed yet.

43:39.360 --> 43:42.360
It's just so hard not being
able to protect you.

43:42.440 --> 43:43.960
Yeah, but you can't.

43:53.040 --> 43:54.120
Mike, wait up.

43:54.200 --> 44:00.040
(upbeat music playing)

44:19.640 --> 44:21.000
Hey, what's up?

44:22.600 --> 44:24.080
I'm gonna get a little knife.

44:24.160 --> 44:25.640
A girl's got to protect herself.

44:25.720 --> 44:28.240
I need heavy artillery,
unlike some people I know.

44:45.280 --> 44:50.800
(serene music playing)

45:25.800 --> 45:30.760
(theme music playing)
